    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <head>No. 150.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 13,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 400.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The action of yourself and Mr. Vignaud, as
                        delegates to the international conference for the protection of submarine
                        cables, as reported in your dispatch No. 441 of the 10th ultimo, is approved
                        by the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
